Russian Equity Movers: Gazprom Neft, Norilsk Nickel, Tatneft

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-03T15:48:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/russian-equity-movers-gazprom-neft-norilsk-nickel-tatneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  plunged 3.4
percent to 1,655.36 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, its
biggest loss since April 18. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
retreated 3.4 percent to 1,901.73.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX), the oil arm of  Russia ’s natural
gas export monopoly, fell the most in 13 months, sliding 5.2
percent to 130.5 rubles. Crude oil for September delivery
dropped $1.91, or 2 percent, to $91.88 a barrel in  New York .  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX), Russia’s biggest mining
company, decreased by its most in more than two months, falling
2.5 percent to 7,250 rubles. Nickel, copper and tin fell on the
London Metal Exchange.  OAO Tatneft (TATN3 RX), the oil producer located in the
Tatarstan region, slid the most since May 2010, losing 5 percent
to 171.64 rubles after oil declined.  To contact the reporter on this story:
